snippet.textDisplay:
The harness is very clearly not the most comfortable thing for the dogs, but the way it wraps and supports the legs at the hips pretty much ensures that the spine isn't under that much pressure. Additionally, they are super securely fastened. This honestly appears to be the most safe thing for a dog in the case of a car accident, because they are secured and supported. Dogs, especially those with body types similar to IGs, are fairly vulnerable in a car accident, but this eliminates the majority of the risk of a dog flying across the car or even being ejected in a minor accident. Is it perfect and comfortable? No. But we humans also do uncomfortable things for ultimate safety.


Honestly, the safest thing (imo) is to limit dogs in cars as much as possible. I really only take mine in the car for vet appointments, but I am fortunate enough to have enough land for them to run around on and a park nearby so I do not necessarily have to drive them to parks so they can have ample room to run and play.
